\tan B &= \frac{AC}{BC} \\
&= \frac{b}{a} \\
&= \frac{\sqrt{c^2 - c^2/\sin^2 \theta}}{c/\sin \theta} \\
&= \sqrt{\frac{\sin^2 \theta - 1/\sin^2 \theta}{\sin^2 \theta}} \\
&= \sqrt{\frac{\sin^4 \theta - 1}{\sin^4 \theta}} \\
&= \boxed{\sqrt{\frac{15}{8}}}.
\end{align*}

Let $\theta = \angle ACB.$  Then $\angle ACD = \theta,$ so $\angle BCD = 2 \theta.$  Similarly, $\angle BCE = \theta$ and $\angle BCE = 2 \theta.$

