Then by the Law of Sines on triangles $BCD$ and $BCE,$
\[\frac{BD}{\sin \theta} = \frac{CD}{\sin 2 \theta} = 2 CD \cos \theta,\]and
\[\frac{BE}{\sin \theta} = \frac{CE}{\sin 2 \theta} = 2 CE \cos \theta.\]Then
\[\frac{BD}{BE} = \frac{CD}{CE} \cdot \frac{\cos \theta}{\cos \theta} = \frac{2 \cos \theta}{1 - 2 \cos^2 \theta}.\]Also, $BD + DE = BE,$ so
\[\frac{BD}{BE - BD} = \frac{8}{15}.\]Let $x = \cos^2 \theta.$  Then $BD/BE = 2x/(1 - 2x),$ and $BD/(BE - BD) = 8/7.$  Solving, we find $x = \cos^2 \theta = \frac{3}{5}.$  Then $\sin^2 \theta = 1 - \cos^2 \theta = \frac{2}{5},$ so
\[\tan^2 B = \frac{\sin^2 B}{\cos^2 B} = \frac{\sin^2 \theta}{1 - \sin^2 \theta} = \frac{2/5}{3/5} = \frac{2}{3}.\]Since $B$ is acute, $\tan B = \boxed{\sqrt{\frac{2}{3}}}.$

