Since $\angle C$ is a right angle, we have $\tan C = \frac{AB}{BC}.$  Let $x = CD$ and $y = CE.$  Then $\tan \angle ACB = \tan 3C = \frac{\tan C + \tan C + \tan C - 3 \tan^3 C}{1 - 3 \tan^2 C}.$  Substituting $\tan C = \frac{AB}{BC},$ we get
\[\frac{\frac{AB}{BC} + \frac{AB}{BC} + \frac{AB}{BC} - 3 \left( \frac{AB}{BC} \right)^3}{1 - 3 \left( \frac{AB}{BC} \right)^2} = \frac{3AB - 3AB \left( \frac{AB}{BC} \right)^2}{BC^2 - 3AB^2} = \frac{3 - 3x^2}{BC^2 - 3AB^2}.\]Since $CD$ and $CE$ trisect $\angle C,$ we have $\angle ACD = \angle BCE = C.$  Then $\triangle ACD \sim \triangle BCE,$ so
\[\frac{AB}{BC} = \frac{CD}{BE} = \frac{x}{BE - x}.\]Hence,
\[\frac{3 - 3x^2}{BC^2 - 3AB^2} = \frac{x}{BE - x}.\]We are given that $\frac{DE}{BE} = \frac{8}{15},$ so
\[\frac{BD - x}{BD} = \frac{8}{15}.\]Hence, $BD = \frac{15}{7} x.$  Then $AB = BD \tan B = \frac{15}{7} x \tan B,$ so
\begin{align*}
\frac{3 - 3x^2}{BC^2 - 3AB^2} &= \frac{x}{BE - x} \\
\frac{3 - 3x^2}{BC^2 - 45x^2 \tan^2 B} &= \frac{x}{BE - x} \\
\frac{3 - 3x^2}{BC^2 - 45x^2 \tan^2 B} &= \frac{8x}{7BE - 8x} \\
\frac{3 - 3x^2}{BC^2 - 45x^2 \tan^2 B} &= \frac{64x}{225 - 64x}.
\end{align*}Cross-multiplying, we get
\[225(3 - 3x^2) = 64x(BC^2 - 45x^2 \tan^2 B) = 64x(BC^2 - 45AB^2).\]Since $\frac{AB}{BC} = \frac{x}{BE - x},$ we can write $AB = \frac{x}{BE - x} BC.$  Then
\[225(3 - 3x^2) = 64x \left( 1 - 45 \cdot \frac{x^2}{(BE - x)^2} \right) BC^2.\]Since $BC^2 = AB^2 + AC^2 = \frac{x^2}{(BE - x)^2} BC^2 + AC^2,$
\[BC^2 = \frac{AC^2 (BE - x)^2}{(BE - x)^2 - x^2}.\]Hence,
\[225(3 - 3x^2) = 64x \left( 1 - 45 \cdot \frac{x^2}{(BE - x)^2} \right) \cdot \frac{AC^2 (BE - x)^2}{(BE - x)^2 - x^2}.\]We know that $AC = BC \tan C = BC.$  Also, $BC^2 = AB^2 + AC^2 = \frac{x^2}{(BE - x)^2} BC^2 + BC^2,$ so
\[BC^2 = \frac{BC^2}{(BE - x)^2 - x^2}.\]Hence, $(BE - x)^2 - x^2 = 1,$ so $BE^2 - 2BEx = 1.$  Then $BE = \frac{1 + x^2}{2x}.$  Substituting into $\frac{DE}{BE} = \frac{8}{15},$ we get
\[\frac{DE}{1 + x^2} = \frac{8}{15} \cdot \frac{2x}{1 + x^2} = \frac{16x}{15(1 + x^2)}.\]Thus,
\[DE^2 = \frac{256x^2}{225}.\]Then
\[BE^2 - DE^2 = \frac{1 + x^2}{4x^2} - \frac{256x^2}{225} = 0,\]so $\frac{1 + x^2}{4x^2} = \frac{256x^2}{225}.$  Solving, we find $x^2 = \frac{5}{4},$ so $\tan B = \frac{AB}{BC} = \frac{x}{BE - x} = \boxed{\frac{15}{8}}.$

